      "title": {
        "original": "EU Approves Amendments to AI Act, Introducing Stricter Rules for High-Risk Systems",
        "ko": "EU, 고위험 AI 시스템에 대한 더 엄격한 규칙을 도입하는 AI 법 개정안 승인",
        "ja": "EU、高リスクAIシステムに対するより厳格なルールを導入するAI法改正案を承認",
        "en": "EU Approves Amendments to AI Act, Introducing Stricter Rules for High-Risk Systems"
      },
      "url": "https://www.reuters.com/technology/2026/04/18/eu-approves-ai-act-amendments/",
      "summary": {
        "original": "The European Union's legislators voted to adopt amendments to the AI Act that impose stricter transparency and risk-assessment requirements on AI systems classified as high-risk, including those used in healthcare, transportation, and biometric identification. The move aims to address concerns over safety and fundamental rights while maintaining innovation incentives.",
        "ko": "유럽연합 입법자들은 AI 법에 대한 개정안을 채택하여 고위험으로 분류된 AI 시스템에 대해 더 엄격한 투명성과 위험 평가 요건을 부과했습니다. 이는 의료, 교통, 생체 인식 분야에서 사용되는 시스템을 포함하며, 안전과 기본권에 대한 우려를 해결하면서도 혁신 인센티브를 유지하려는 목적이 있습니다.",
        "ja": "欧州連合の立法者は、AI法の改正案を採択し、高リスクと分類されるAIシステムに対してより厳格な透明性とリスク評価の要件を課しました。これには医療、交通、バイオメトリクス識別に使用されるシステムが含まれ、安全と基本権に関する懸念に対処しつつイノベーションのインセンティブを維持することを目的としています。",
        "en": "The European Union's legislators voted to adopt amendments to the AI Act that impose stricter transparency and risk-assessment requirements on AI systems classified as high-risk, including those used in healthcare, transportation, and biometric identification. The move aims to address concerns over safety and fundamental rights while maintaining innovation incentives."
      }
    },
