        "en": "Researchers Achieve Quantum Supremacy with 1,000-Qubit Processor"
      },
      "url": "https://www.bbc.com/news/technology-20260418-quantum-supremacy",
      "summary": {
        "original": "A team from the University of Tokyo and IBM announced they have performed a computational task that would take the world's fastest supercomputer over 10,000 years using a newly developed 1,000-qubit superconducting processor, marking a milestone in quantum supremacy. The experiment demonstrated error rates below 0.1% and validated quantum advantage for specific optimization problems.",
        "ko": "도쿄대와 IBM 연구팀은 newly developed 1,000큐비트 초전도 프로세서를 사용하여 세계에서 가장 빠른 슈퍼컴퓨터보다 10,000년 이상 걸릴 작업을 수행했다고 발표하며, 양자 우월성의 이정표를 세웠습니다. 이 실험은 오류율이 0.1% 미만을示했으며, 특정 최적화 문제에 대한 양자 우위를 입증했습니다.",
        "ja": "東京大学とIBMの研究チームは、新たに開発された1,000量子ビット超伝導プロセッサーを用いて、世界最速のスーパーコンピューターでは10,000年以上かかる計算タスクを実行し、量子優越性のマイルストーンを達成したと発表しました。この実験では誤差率が0.1%未満を示し、特定の最適化問題における量子優位性を実証しました。",
        "en": "A team from the University of Tokyo and IBM announced they have performed a computational task that would take the world's fastest supercomputer over 10,000 years using a newly developed 1,000-qubit superconducting processor, marking a milestone in quantum supremacy. The experiment demonstrated error rates below 0.1% and validated quantum advantage for specific optimization problems."
      }
